<section class="section surface-steel">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header section-header--center">
      <span class="eyebrow">The plant vehicle problem</span>
      <h2 class="display-m">Forklifts are the highest-incident equipment in most plants.</h2>
      <p>Roughly one in ten plant injuries involves a forklift, and the causes are remarkably consistent. Most plants have no real-time visibility into any of them.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:20px;max-width:920px;margin:0 auto;">
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--steel-200);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;"><div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:11px;background:rgba(240,80,112,0.10);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:16px;"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F05070" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 2"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3" stroke-opacity="0.4"/></svg></div><h3 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.3;min-height:1.3em;">Hidden hotspots</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--steel-700);line-height:1.55;">Incidents cluster at the same blind corners, congested intersections, and shift-change zones. The pattern sits in your data unread, invisible to the team that could act on it.</p></div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--steel-200);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;"><div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:11px;background:rgba(25,167,206,0.12);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:16px;"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#19A7CE" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="8" r="4"/><path d="M5 21v-2a4 4 0 0 1 4-4h6a4 4 0 0 1 4 4v2"/><path d="M9 9l-2-2M15 9l2-2"/></svg></div><h3 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.3;min-height:1.3em;">Unverified operators</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--steel-700);line-height:1.55;">A vehicle key in the wrong hands is the most common starting point for a serious incident. Most plants have no automatic check that the person at the wheel is trained and authorised.</p></div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--steel-200);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;"><div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:11px;background:rgba(26,39,68,0.09);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:16px;"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#1A2744" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="5" y="3" width="14" height="18" rx="2"/><path d="M9 7h6M9 11h6M9 15h3"/><path d="M16 17l2 2 3-3" stroke="#F05070"/></svg></div><h3 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.3;min-height:1.3em;">No pre-trip discipline</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--steel-700);line-height:1.55;">The mandated daily safety check often becomes a tick-box on paper, when it happens at all. Defects find you the hard way, in the middle of a shift.</p></div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--steel-200);border-radius:12px;padding:28px;"><div style="width:48px;height:48px;border-radius:11px;background:rgba(240,80,112,0.10);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:16px;"><svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F05070" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M5 17H3v-5l2-5h11l3 5h2v5h-2"/><circle cx="7.5" cy="17.5" r="2"/><circle cx="17.5" cy="17.5" r="2"/><path d="M21 6l-3 3M21 9l-3-3"/></svg></div><h3 style="font-size:17px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:8px;line-height:1.3;min-height:1.3em;">Behaviour you cannot see</h3><p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--steel-700);line-height:1.55;">Rash driving, harsh braking, overspeeding, and fatigue go unnoticed until a near-miss escalates. By the time it shows in an incident report, the chance to coach is gone.</p></div>
