    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-item" open><summary class="faq-q">Do you require hardware on the forklifts?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. Forklift Safety uses a small in-vehicle device for accurate location tracking and operator behaviour detection, unlike Driving Safety, which runs on smartphone sensors. The hardware is straightforward to install and is included in the deployment package.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Does it work with all forklift types?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes, counterbalance, reach trucks, order pickers, pallet trucks, and powered tugs. We've deployed across electric and IC forklifts, indoor and outdoor configurations.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">How does hotspot mapping work?</summary><div class="faq-a">The platform aggregates location data from all forklifts and overlays incident events (collisions, near-misses, harsh events, speed violations). Zones with elevated event density become hotspots, and you can drill into the underlying events to understand why.</div></details>
      <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-q">Can we integrate with our WMS or ERP?</summary><div class="faq-a">Yes. SAP, Oracle, and most major warehouse management systems integrate via standard APIs. Operator-level data syncs with HRIS for review cycles.</div></details>
